    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Your companion is a stocky-limbed lizard with a long, almost serpentine body.</p>\n<p><strong>Size</strong> Medium</p>\n<p><strong>Melee</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">a </span>jaws, <strong>Damage</strong> 1d8 piercing</p>\n<p><strong>Str</strong> +3, <strong>Dex</strong> +2, <strong>Con</strong> +2, <strong>Int</strong> -4, <strong>Wis</strong> +1, <strong>Cha</strong> +0</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Points</strong> 8</p>\n<p><strong>Skill</strong> Survival</p>\n<p><strong>Senses</strong> low-light vision, scent (imprecise) 30 feet</p>\n<p><strong>Speed</strong> 30 feet</p>\n<p><strong>Special</strong> mount</p>\n<p><strong>Support Benefit</strong> The monitor lizard distracts an adjacent opponent with snapping jaws and rapid movements. Until the start of your next turn, if your Strike damages a foe, any time the foe attempts an action with the manipulate trait until the end of your next turn, it must attempt a DC 5 flat check. On a failure, the action is disrupted.</p>\n<p><strong>Advanced Maneuver</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-animal-companions.AC-Advanced-Maneuvers.uR3j6TAJFeOVUHpY]{Lurching Rush}</p>"
